rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A measure of wind speed that is correlated with observed conditions on land or water. There are thirteen values in the scale, ranging from 0 "calm" to 13 "hurricane force".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beaufort Wind Force

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a value of the Beaufort Scale to the average wind speed for that value.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a value of the Beaufort Scale to the minimum wind speed for that value.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a value of the Beaufort Scale to corresponding tropical cyclone categories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone Categories

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a value of the Beaufort Scale with the average height of waves for the value.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wave Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for classifications of clouds, e.g. Cumulus and Altostratus.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cloud

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cloud classification to the maximum height in meters at which clouds of this type form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Altitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a cloud classification to the minimum height in meters at which clouds of this type form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Altitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether clouds of the given classification are capable of producing precipitation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Precipitation
Cloud classification
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. The existing type meteorology.cloud can be used for all cloud classifications. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:meteorology.cloud]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cyclone-affected area
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Use location.location instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: cyclones
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to location.location. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all mso:meteorology.floods. Floods are the overflow of water that submerges usually dry land.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flood
Forecast Zone
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Use location.location instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The meteorological service that uses this forecast zone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Service
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added directly to location.location. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A qualitative description of the amount of the moon that is visible to an observer on Earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lunar Phase

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Up to 50% of the right side of the moon is visible.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The entire moon is visible.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Full Moon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: None of the moon is visible.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: New Moon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Up to 50% of the left side of the moon is visible.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Third Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization or a department within another organization that is responsible for issuing weather forecasts and/or weather alerts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meteorological Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a meteorological service to the locations for which the service provides weather forecasts, alerts, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forecast Zones

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a meteorological service to a tropical cyclone category used by the service in forecasts and alerts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone Categories

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all tornadoes. Tornadoes are the rotating columns of air that are in contact with the earth and a cloud and typically take the form of a funnel. Most tornadoes have wind speeds of less than 110 mph, but in some cases they can reach speeds of more than 300 mph.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tornado

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:meteorology.tornado to its rating on the enhanced fajita scale.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fujita Scale (Enhanced)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:meteorology.tornado to the distance the tornado travelled on land.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Path Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all cyclones. These are characterized by inward spiraling winds that rotate anti-clockwise in the Northern Hemisphere and clockwise in the Southern Hemisphere of the Earth. Most large-scale cyclonic circulations are centered on areas of low atmospheric pressure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone to a location that was impacted by the tropical cyclone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Affected Area

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a tropical cyclone to its corresponding category. Note that different agencies categorize storms differently, so a single storm may correspond to more than one category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone to a dated money value representing the total damages caused by the cyclone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Damages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone to the date that the storm disappeared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dissipated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to the date that the storm first appeared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Formed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone to the speed of the strongest wind gusts in kilometers per hour that were observed in the storm.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Highest Winds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone to the lowest atmospheric pressure in millibars that was observed in the storm.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lowest Pressure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a tropical cyclone to the tropical cyclone season when the storm appeared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains standard designations for kinds of tropical cyclones. These include the categories of the Saffir-Simpson Scale, RSMC Tokyo's Tropical Cyclone Intensity Scale, and others.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to a corresponding value of the Beaufort Scale.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beaufort Force

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to the maximum amount in meters that the height of the sea is expected to increase as a result of a storm having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Storm Surge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to the maximum sustained wind speed in kilometers per hour of a storm having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to the maximum wind speed in kilometers per hour of gusts in a storm having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to a meteorological agency that uses this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meteorological Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to the minimum amount in meters that the height of the sea is expected to increase as a result of a storm having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Storm Surge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to the minimum sustained wind speed in kilometers per hour of a storm having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone category to the minimum wind speed in kilometers per hour of gusts in a storm having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a tropical cyclone category to a particular tropical cyclone having this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclones

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing entities that indicate a period of time and a place where tropical cyclones could form, e.g. 1959 Atlantic Hurricane Season or 1992 Pacific Typhoon Season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to the date in the season that the first storm that became a tropical cyclone appeared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Storm Formed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to the date in the season that the last storm that had been a tropical cyclone disappeared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Storm Dissipated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to the number of tropical cyclones in the season having a category of three or higher.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Major Storms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to the most powerful tropical cyclone of the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strongest Storm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to a dated money value representing the total damages caused by tropical cyclones of the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Damages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to a number representing how many people died from tropical cyclones of the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Fatalities

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to a number representing how many tropical cyclones appeared in the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Storms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tropical cyclone season to a tropical cyclone that appeared in the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tropical Cyclone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A canonical enumeration of qualitatative weather alerts, e.g. tornado_warning, flood_warning, fire_advisory, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Alert

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A canonical enumeration of qualitatative weather conditions, e.g. sunny, partly_cloudy, blizzard, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Condition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all weather events. These are the events that occur due to the atmospheric conditions of temperature, wind, clouds, precipitation, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that is used to collect information about weather forecasts, e.g. the time frame of the forecast, the forecast zone, and the conditions observed or predicted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Forecast

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that relates a weather forecast to a weather alert that is part of the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Alert

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to text that amplifies or specifies the corresponding weather alert.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Alert Description

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted pressure of the atmosphere measured in Pascals for the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Atmospheric Pressure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to cloud classifications associated with the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cloud

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that relates a weather forecast to weather condition(s) observed or predicated in the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Condition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to text that amplifies or specifies the corresponding weather condition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weather Condition Description

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that is used to specify whether the given weather forecast relates to daytime (value of 1) or nighttime (value of 0) for a given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day or Night

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the temperature at which water begins to condense according to the conditions of the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dewpoint

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property used to relate one weather forecast to another forecast, e.g. a one-hour forecast that is part of a day forecast or a day forecast that is part of a five-day or ten-day forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forecast Element

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the end of the time range covered by the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forecast End

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to a measure of temperature in degrees celsius which takes into account factors that make the actual temperature seem warmer or colder, e.g. wind chill.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Feels Like Temperature

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the highest observed or predicted air temperature in degrees celsius for the given forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: High Temperature

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the lowest observed or predicted air temperature in degrees celsius for the given forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Low Temperature

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to a qualitative description of the amount of the moon that is visible to an observer on Earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lunar Phase

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the service that issued the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meteorological Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the time of the first appearance of the moon over the Earth's horizon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Moonrise

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the time of the last appearance of the moon over the Earth's horizon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Moonset

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the number of days covered by the weather forecast, typically 1 day, 5 days or 10 days.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Days

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that relates a weather forecast to the place that the forecast is about.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Place

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted quantity of pollen in the atmosphere, measured in grams per cubic centimeter. Note that the unit of measurement should eventually be changed to *grams per cubic meter*, because this seems to be standard for pollen counts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pollen Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted quantity of pollution in the atmosphere, measured in grams per cubic centimeter. Note that the unit of measurement should eventually be changed to *grams per cubic meter*, because this seems to be standard for pollution counts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pollution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted precipitation in centimeters for the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Precipitation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the likelihood that there will be measurable precipitation within the specified time frame of the weather forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chance of Precipitation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted relative humidity, i.e. the current absolute humidity divided by the maximum absolute humidity for the given temperature.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relative Humidity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted snowfall in centimeters for the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Snowfall

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the beginning of the time range covered by the forecast.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forecast Start

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the time when the first part of the sun is visible over the eastern horizon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sunrise

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the time when the last part of the sun is visible over the western horizon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sunset

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted air temperature in degrees celsius for the forecast. Note that, when the range of time associated with the forecast is long, the properties meteorology.weather_forecast.high_temperature and meteorology.weather_forecast.low_temperature can be used instead.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Temperature

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted measurement of the strength of ultraviolet radiation from the sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ultraviolet Index

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the distance at which the unaided eye can distinguish certain sorts of objects.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Visibility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted direction of the wind, e.g. North or SSW.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Direction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the highest observed or predicted speed of gusts of wind in kilometers per hour. Note that, for sustained wind speeds, the property meteorology.weather_forecast.wind_speed should be used instead.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Gust

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a weather forecast to the observed or predicted speed of the wind in kilometers per hour. Note that, for wind gusts, the property meteorology.weather_forecast.wind_gust should be used instead.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Speed
